deck_excerpt: A Gren Maju OTK deck, using a big Danger! engine and a Sangan engine.
deck_description: I have fully embraced m o n k e y. Anyway, Gren Maju is a fun OTK deck that doesn't require much effort or intelligence. Pretty simply, you banish tons of cards using Eater, Orochi, Shifter, etc to get a ton of fuel for Gren Maju to go to inane levels of strength and beat through anything and finish off the game fucking easy. I leaned into Dangers! a bit more heavily since I have lots of Danger! cards IRL and I plan on building this IRL, so.  Anyways, Dangers! help a ton with bodies on board and digging through the deck to get Maju, as nothing can search for Maju except for a random XYZ that I opted not to play. I also included a very s p i c y tech here- the Sangan engine. You may be wondering- What the fuck is a Sangan engine? What the fuck is this, GOAT Format? Yea, basically. The Sangan engine is basically where you normal summon Sangan, and send it off for Almiraj for an easy search with a large pool of monsters for combos, and a good monster on board. I included Santa Claws as the main target to out problem monsters, but you can also use it to search some of the Dangers! and handtraps, making Sangan a very generic card for the deck. I also included some generic cards in the extra, mainly generic links, Almiraj for the combo, and rank 8's and fusions to send for the Dogmatika match up. Overall, this is a fun and simple rouge deck that doesn't take much effort. Credits: https://ygoprodeck.com/gren-maju-11/ Big Pimpin's Sangan combo to search for Santa Claws shown on CapG's stream highlights

deck_excerpt: Harpies, Birbs, & the Brigade pair up to shut your opponent down and out.
deck_description:
~~Same as before but with some updates since I've tested it IRL now.~~

Deck only really has struggled so far against Eldlich, & Mystic Mine shut-down. Hence the new side-deck. Deck is very consistent. Does best going first but does fine going 2nd if you lose the dice roll. LOTS of flexibility in play style. End Boards with best to worst scenarios (worst still pretty good stall):
  • Option A: End on Simorgh + Mist Valley + Doom or Rugal & Feather Storm set face-down.
  • Option B: Simorgh + Mist Valley, Hysteric Sign face-down as bait to be popped to search Feather Storm + Channeler & Harpist
  • (rarely) Option C: End with Shuraig, Revolt, Warning Point, or other backrow as bait
  • (worst case) Option D: 1 face-up Wind Wing-Beast (Harpie, Nervall, or Barrier) + 1 Feather Storm  to stall for next turn.
Bait:
  • Monsters: Harpist, Kit, Nervall
  • Spell: Hysteric Sign, Stand-off, Rendezvous
  • Trap: Feather Storm
Side Deck:
  • Simorgh cards are great for Spell/Trap interaction. Bird of Beginning adds one to hand. Dark Simorgh stops backrow setting.
  • Droll & Nibiru if going 2nd.
  • Anti spell/trap cards to break Mystic & disrupt Eldlich
Reason for certain cards:
  1. Underworld: outs most big annoying things ie. Dragoon
  2. Zerofyne: Dark ruler in a card +ATK boost & still deal damage same-turn
  3. Doom Eagle: Tri-brigade friendly, clears out opponent graveyard sources, + OTK enabler
  4. Almiraj: Brick help - sends to grave Nervall, Kit, and (at worst) Bird of Beginning
  5. WHY? Warning Point instead of Imperm: Going against a deck like Dragon-Link where even if you have a great board they can break it 2nd turn and still go-off. Slows down their summoning & attacks. You can side Imperms if you know you're going 2nd though. Up to you.
Possible Variations:
  1. Like brigade better? Run less harpies but still keep some essentials: Perfumer, egotist, Harpie Lady (any variant), Harpist, Conductor, & (of course) Feather Storm.
  2. Want more Simorgh? Swap out harpies for some birbs.
  3. Want more beasts? Sub-in Rescue cat, Kalantosa, & Valerifawn.
  4. Finally, you can always also swap another Simorgh for the second Shuraig. I'm still trying both and neither is necessarily 'better'. Shuraig is beneficial when destroyed though, Simorgh is not.
SUMMARY If you love Harpies but hate their death by hand-trap & brick-city weaknesses, Harpie + Brigade is for you. You can easily search  & run 3-of the best Trap (imo) of all time: Feather Storm. AND, you can use destruction & banishing from opponents as an advantage!

So, this is my Phantom Knight Deck.  I think Phantom Knights are better in the current Meta game. Sure it wont win any matches, but it is very versatile. In my opinion Phantom Knights can hold on to Eldlichs resource game, to a certain degree, the matchup against Dino is evenly matched, but yeah Dragon Link is just unplayable most of the time. Against rogue decks it it is very good, you have a good otk you can pull up many disruptions on first turn and can wall up against heavy otk decks (most of the rogue decks just can set up a good otk) like Cyber Dragons.  As you can see I play two break swords and two cherubini, I do this for more recurtion and resource management. Also, you can see I don´t play Dragun, if you want to play the package it makes the deck better, but I believe Dragun should be banned it is a game breaking card and I do not want to support this card. I know its paradox to say something like this while playing Zeus, but you have to play some of these game breaking cards in order to compete and I think Dragun is even more toxic.  So obviously you can change so cards here, I like the deck how I build it, but I want to recommend so change, first obviously the dragun package, secondly ou can play farfa and take out the foolish and thirdly, you can play leviair for more consistency.  Please let me know if you like it or not and why, so we can develop our deck building skills.

deck_excerpt: Main focus of this deck: fast Synchro Summons and Destruction.
deck_description: A randomly build Blackwing fun deck, I thought of no special strategy in particular when I made this. In short it is a Blackwing deck about getting Synchro's out at a fast rate, it is kind of old school with "Bora The Spear", "Sirocco The Dawn" and cards like Gale and Fiendish Chain. But with modern additions like Assault Blackwing Kunai, Decay The Ill Wind. Main focus of the deck: fast Synchro Summons and Destruction Important/useful Combos: Classics as Bora + Gale insta. Synchro LVL: 7 or an easy LVL: 8 Synchro via Decay + with most of the other Blackwings. Nearly every Blackwing that can Special summon itself for a very fast Synchro.                                                          "Black Whirlwind" the most powerful search card for Blackwings for when you can't Special on the 1st Turn or anytime else. Sirocco's effect for  a impressive ATK  boost for 1 other Blackwing, but locks you into attacking with the powerd up monster only. Other Powerful tools: "Icarus Attack" a very useful card with the low cost of tributing 1 of your Monster for destroying up to 2 cards, and getting another Blackwing out is easy thus making the cost almost 0. "Sirocco" + "Bora" + other "Blackwing" on the field with "Kalut The Moon Shadow"' effect from your hand for a possible OTK or at least severe damage. "Allure Of Darkness" lets you draw 2 cards by banishing 1 Dark Attribute monster from your hand, that makes it 100% better then "Cards for Black Feathers" which prohibits you from Special Summoning for that turn. Last but not least Synchros: this deck consists of a wide range of Synchro monsters which includes, Classics as "Blackwing Armor Master" and "Stardust Dragon" also powerful cards like "Blackwing Raikiri The Rain Shower" with it you can destroy up to 4 cards per turn if you got a full set of 5 Blackwings on the field, which is quite easy to achieve. Other notable cards are, "Red Dragon Archfiend" for blowing up the opponents defending monsters or "Blackwing Full Armor Master" for dealing with effect monsters. thats it I hope this deck is of any use for this is my first deck I will upload on here, it will  definitely not be my last one! feel free to rate this deck or you may explain to me and everyone else things that could be changed or what I missed. In best regards AvianCompanion23

deck_excerpt: Six Samurai: Semi-infinite Master Combo !! Come and meet him.
deck_description: The idea of this deck is to make semi-infinite summons in order to fill the field with the synchro Shien and, with support for negation (Number 106) and to increase the attack of the warriors (Ferocious Flame Swordsman). So having an excellent field in the first round to block your opponent's moves. Playing in the second round can guarantee an OTK, but you are more likely to be blocked by your opponent, which can end up breaking the combo.   Use Shogun to search for the "Gateway of the Six" or another card that can place "Bushido Counters" to facilitate the combo. The counters will help you to search and summon the "Kizan" or the "Grandmaster" to recover the spent counters and continue the combo.   Use Isolde to summon a "Fuhma" straight from the deck to the field so that you can do another Shien synchro. If you are lucky with your hand, it is possible to make three Shiens. Since the normal thing about this combo is that you leave two in the field.   The other monsters (Number 106 and F. Flame Swordsman) you can normally summon by following the combo. The first using two "Kizans" and the second using one "Kizan" and one "Grandmaster". Tip: Never summon monsters that you will not remove from the field in the link zone that Shogun points to. Well, Shogun assists you by adding counters when you call the "Six Samurai" in your link zone. Only at the end, when you are finishing the combo with "Number 106" and "F. Flame Swordsman", is it free to summon. Because at this point, you will already have your monster zone full.   That's it guys, I hope you enjoy the deck. Patience to hit the combo and be careful not to get excited about the combo too. See you on the next deck.

You have so many ways to extend, that you should always be able to fall back onto Spheres and Dragoon, but ideally also I:P. That takes a minimum of just 6 monsters and I:P can link itself Verte and the summon from Spheres, for either of our Link 5's.  If u want to play LV10 Turbo, just cut the Dark Dragoon stuff, for 2 more LV7 and LV10. Maybe also 1 LV5 to send off Pile and search LV7. Basically just get Saryuja to summon LV7 for you and skip the LV ups lol.  I find this version more fun, jamming as many extenders and link 2 bosses as I can. Have fun!! =]     In lieu of a strict combo guide, I offer this checklist of things to do on any turn:  BLACK METAL / SEYFERT - This is the best starter, especially because you can, uhh, start searching your Red-eyes fusion stuff if you loop Black Metal then shuffle them back with Saryuja for extra advantage LOL. the line goes Black Metal > Striker Dragon > REDMD > Black Metal > Romulus. Seyfert does the same thing, but doesnt get us the extra plus.  ROMULUS - This card gets Ravine which sends Absorouter, which gets Tracer. If you draw either Ravine or Absorouter, just skip Romulus or use Ravine to discard Absorouter. Next you can summon Tracer using Boot Sector Launch.  SARYUJA - So, to make Saryuja here we actually need 1 extender after the Romulus play. We can keep playing without one, by using Tracer to pop Boot Sector, but that locks us into Darks, Saryuja and Spheres are both Light. If you have an extender, summon Elpy next to Striker then use Elpy to get a 4th monster.  ELPY - My favorite Elpy target is Seyfert, which is why I only play the 1, but Tempest, Pile Armed, and Black/Darkness Metal all do the same basic thing. To avoid getting locked into dragons, link off Elpy into Saryuja, then after using Pisty late in the combo (ideally for Tracer or just Rokket Synchron if you already used it) link that off for Spheres. If you make Spheres first, you have to use both Guardragons before Saryuja, to link them off, or go into Borrelend early.  PILE ARMED - Pile Armed Dragon either searches Armed Dragon Flash, or draws 1, its nuts. It makes a great starter or extender at any time, as long as you have the send for it. Any Armed Dragon, Tempest or Absorouter are the best discards. Otherwise, Saryuja is the best way to summon it, letting you get the plus without discarding.  TEMPEST - This along with Pile Armed are the best ways for us to get to our Synchros. This is one of the last monsters you re-summon at the end of you combos when you need that one last non-link for I:P or Verte. Tempest is also the alternate send off Ravine if you draw Absorouter.  CHAOS RULER - If you know you have the Light and Dark to resummon it (pretty much if you got to Seyfert) you should always go for this card. You can make it with Tracer+a chaos dragon, or Synchron+Pile Armed/Tempest. The excavate greatly helps to find Tempest and the add will usually hit Veiler, or a Rokket, but can hit Noctovision at best! The resummon is what makes it really strong, and if you pull it off should let you end on Hot Red D and Dark Dragoon with ease.  Once you do all of that, it's time to link away or synchro whatever is left, ideally ending on Heiratic Seal of Heavenly Spheres, I:P Masquerena, Red-Eyes Dark Dragoon, and Hot Red Dr. Abyss. With this, I:P can link itself, Verte, the monster Spheres will summon, and one opponent's monster for Underworld Goddess of the Closed World, or for Borrelend Dragon.

deck_excerpt: a VAGULEY Egyptian themes chaos deck, revolving around multiple archetypes (ew, I know). You should really read the further description by clicking th
deck_description: Hi! I made a new deck. You may look at this decklist, and perhaps scoff (lol), or at least think this deck is sub-par, but, I believe I can show you how this can be an incredible and powerful deck. Or it may be crap, in which case, screw me. If you don't know me https://ygoprodeck.com/best-of-blue-eyes-re-make/ and https://ygoprodeck.com/amazing-ancient-gears/ are some of the better decks I've made. Please, check them out (or do not, I am not a beggar) As for this deck, let's get into it for real. Your end goal is to cause Armageddon or just the plain old end, with any of your chaos emperor dragon's. Now, I don't like archetypes, I'm not sure why, so there are plenty cards in here that are just here, some people don't like that, but I hope some of you can appreciate that. It's not just a decklist copied and pasted from the internet, and it's not using the same 4 words or same 2 monsters. Two other monsters you can use to take out you opponents, are Ma'at, and Mythical beast master Cerberus. Now, this deck was gone for sort of an Egyptian theme (vaguely mind you), I picked out some more Egyptian themed powerful monster's, without going Egyptian god or Exodia, or even the creator route. Ma'at is summoned using a light dragon, and a light fairy, for the dragon part of that, we have Radiant Vouirescensce (perhaps spelled incorrectly) which will also come in use for other monsters. For the fairy we have out Parshaths, not counting the dark counterpart, and Honest, again, dismissing the dark version. Honest can be moved back and forth between the hand, and onto the field once per turn, so you can have it attack you opponent if given the chance, then in your main phase two, bring it back to your hand if you have a stronger monster on the field as well, and you don't want honest to be vulnerable. On top of that, a monster of the Light attribute, can absorb it's enemies attack, using honest's effect while in the hand, and this is all the same for dark honest as well. Both honest and dark honest work well with the strongest members of this deck, the chaotic kings, Ma'at, and even the mythical beasts, powering them up, and being the right attributes to help summon at least some, if not most of them. Airknight and Darknight parshath as well, although to a slightly smaller extent, and they get better with neo parshath. While were almost on the topic of mythical beasts, let's jump all the way there, because some people might be confused as to their addition to this deck. Why are they here? Because their cool, powerful, easy to summon, and one of them is a jackal, an animal famous for being an Egyptian creature. Getting Mythical beast master Cerberus should be simple, just, like, draw it, and add it to your pendulum zone, when hopefully your Chaos dragon isn't there. Next up, with it's effect, send it to the extra deck, and bring forth your King Jackal, which can use it's effect, and we'll get to see our old friend Master Cerberus once again, this time on the field, able to destroy your enemies, which is boosted by the many spell cards within the deck, including Power of the guardians. Some spells include Gold sarcophagus, good if you need a specific card, which you often will, Twin twisters, to get rid of those pesky trap/spells your opponent has, raigeki, old school, but watch your opponents monsters be a annihilated, and card advance, since it's nice to know what's coming up ahead, and it works wonders for Ma'at's ability, so you don't just have to guess. I would recommend old summoning Ma'at if you have or used card advance and know what's coming up. Finally, chaos time. Radiant Vouirescensce can be summoned, sending more of it to the grave, one of which can become dark, and boom, immediate way to summon our chaos emperors. Chaos creator and Valkery also help, being of the same archetype. With envoy, or any really of your chaos dragons, destroy everything on the field and in the hand, just obliterate your opponent, and then strike. Simple. Chaotic. Real quick, let me acknowledge the triple sticks, Gather your mind, and Hyena. Both of them are for deck shortening, and yes, when it comes to it, stalling. Lot's of specific cards are needed in this deck, so using gather your mind and hyena can make the amount of cards you need to look through minimal. Also, both have vaguely Egyptian themes. I believe that's it, it's better to play it, test this deck on Duel Nexus, or at home with your own cards, at a card store (stay safe though), test it, edit it, leave suggestions in the comments, tell me what I did wrong, what I did right, what you think of the deck, and feel free to check out my others as well. Thank you very much for reading if you've come this far, and have a good day.

deck_name: Dragon Link Flare - Beelze Loop FTK
deck_excerpt: The dragons have created their ultimate weapon. Plunge your opponent into an endless spiral of pain! OwO Los dragones han creado su arma definitiva.
deck_description:
Deck creado por: Darklab Objetivo: Invocar a Beelze of the Diabolic Dragons y Red-Eyes Flare Metal Dragon para crear un loop de burn infinito! OwO Link a la demostración del Deck:  >>>>  https://youtu.be/_1ARtuZ6qDU  <<<< Requisitos para iniciar el combo: Al final se necesitará varios dragones, pero éstos son fáciles de spamear en la baraja. Siempre la idea es ir por Romulus y los Guardragon para acceder a sus efectos de spam y traer a Black Metal Dragon para obtener a los Red-Eyes. Extenders para iniciar el combo:
  • Absorouter Dragon: Se invoca solo si controlamos un Rokket, lo cual es sencillo. Aún así, siempre se puede enviar al cementerio para añadirnos un Rokket a la mano.
  • Noctovision Dragon: Se invoca solo si invocamos otro dragón de modo especial. Además, cuando se va del campo, nos da un robo!
  • Black Dragon Collapserpent: Se invoca gratis removiendo un monstruo de luz, además nos trae a Wyverburster.
  • White Dragon Wyverburster: Se invoca gratis removiendo un monstruo de oscuridad, además nos trae a Collapserpent.
  • Supreme King Dragon Darkwurm: Se invoca gratis del cementerio, por lo que es el target preferido de Foolish Burial y Dragon Shrine.
  • Starliege Dragon Seyfert: Una invocación normal excelente, ya que con su efecto tendremos en mano a Collapserpent o Wyverburster.
  • Rokket Tracer: Normal Summon de último recurso, además de tener excelentes interacciones con Section Boot y Absorouter. Y es tuner!
  • Black Metal Dragon: Se usa de Normal Summon. Nos añade un Red Eyes, lo cual nos permite usar el Rokket Tracer como extender.
  • One For One: Nos trae a Black Metal Dragon.
  • Dragon Shrine y Foolish Burial: Ver Darkwurm.
  • Monster Reborn: Nos da un cuerpo adicional.
  • Chaos Space: Efecto similar a Seyfert, pero sin gastar la Normal Summon.
  • Quick Revolve: Nos trae a Rokket Tracer gratis.
  • Guardragon of the World Legacy: Efecto similar a Monster Reborn, pero además nos permite mover a un dragón (por lo general un Guardragon).
  • Borrel Regenerator: Nos permite reciclar a Rokket Tracer, por lo que se le puede usar antes como extender.
Pros:
  • Deck bastante consistente.
  • El deck tiene un burn infinito, por lo que no importa cuántos LP tenga el oponente, igual perderá.
  • El deck tiene tan sólo 1 garnet (Red Eyes Fusion), que incluso es posible devolver con Unicorn.
  • El deck tiene extenders muy poderosos, por lo que es posible que sobren recursos en mano.
  • Puede baitear hantraps con los extenders suficientes.
  • Versátil. Es fácil adaptarse a distintos recursos en mano.
Contras:
  • El deck depende de varias adiciones específicas a la mano. Si nos niegan alguna, será gg.
  • Por la naturaleza del deck, éste no tiene acceso a protección.
  • El deck es susceptible a Nibiru, Called by the grave y Ghost Belle, al igual que a Veiler e Impermanence si los usan correctamente.
  • El deck consume varios extenders, por lo que es necesaria una buena mano para realizar los combos.

deck_excerpt: Meta, but also really fun to play with. OTK or control.
deck_description:
A. Cyber Dragon Infinity + Chimeratech Rampage Dragon ⇒ OTK B. Cyber Dragon Infinity + Red-Eyes Dark Dragoon ⇒ Control C. Cyber Dragon Infinity + Constellar Pleiades ⇒ Control
  • Cyber Dragon Sieger:
    • get additional damage for an OTK
    • deal with high atk monster in the field
  • Chimeratech Fortress Dragon:
    • deal with machine annoying monsters in the field
    • if there's an annoying non machine monster ⇒ Jizukiru, the Star Destroying Kaiju
  • Chimeratech Megafleet Dragon:
    • deal with annoying monster in the extra monster zone
  • Chimeratech Overdragon
    • surprise card when you have no cards in the field
    • use Cyber Dragon Core to search Cyberload Fusion
    • return banished cards to your deck
  • Cyber Eternity Dragon
    • if everything else did not work
    • hold the game
    • special summon a cyber dragon from deck, GY or hand
    • banish it to do safe fusion summons
modify
Modify

This deck is really versatile, so you will need to choose the best play for each situation, but it`s really hard to make a bad play. I`ll leave some ideas below, for two combos. note: both combos follow not considering hand traps.
  • Starliege Seyfert + World Legacy Guardragon (WLG) + 3 random cards:
    • normal summon Seyfert
    • activate Seyfert`s effect ⇒ Black Dragon Collapserpent to your hand
    • activate WLG and special summon Seyfert
    • Link Seyfert to Striker Dragon ⇒ add Boot Sector Launch to your hand
    • special summon Black Dragon by banishing Seyfert from your GY
    • Link Black Dragon and Striker Dragon to Hieratic Seal of the Heavenly Spheres
    • activate Black Dragon`s effect ⇒ White Dragon Wyverburster to your hand
    • special summon White Dragon by banishing Black Dragon
    • Link White Dragon to Guardragon Elpy
    • activate WLG`s effect ⇒ move Elpy to below the Seal
    • activate Elpy`s effect ⇒ special summon Omni Dragon Brotaur
    • activate Brotaur`s effect ⇒ target Brotaur ⇒ add Chaos Dragon Levianeer to your hand
    • Link Brotaur to Guardragon Pisty (to the right of Elpy)
    • activate Pisty`s effect ⇒ special summon Seyfert from the banished cards
    • Link Elpy and Pisty to Dragunity Knight - Romulus
    • activate Romulus effect ⇒ add Dragon Ravine to your hand
    • special summon Levianeer by banishing 3 dark monsters from your GY
    • Link Romulus, Levianeer and Seyfert to an Apollusa, Bow of the Goddess (3 negates)
    • activate Ravine ⇒ activate Ravine`s effect ⇒ send 1 card from your hand to the GY ⇒ send Absorouter Dragon to the GY
    • activate Absorouter`s effect ⇒ add Rokket Tracer to your hand
      • if you already have Rokket Tracer in your hand, add Rokket Recharger
    • activate Boot Sector Launch ⇒ activate Boot Sector Launch`s effect ⇒  special summon Rokket Tracer from your hand
    • activate Rokket Tracer`s effect ⇒ target WLG ⇒ special summon Rokket Recharger
    • Synchro summon Borreload Salvage Dragon with Tracer and Recharger
    • activate Borreload Salvage`s effect ⇒ target Romulus
    • final: Hieratic Seal + Borreload Salvage (2 neg) + Apollusa (3 neg)
  • Seyfert + 4 random cards:
    • normal summon Seyfert
    • activate Seyfert's effect ⇒ send Seyfert to the GY ⇒ add Black Dragon to your hand
    • special summon Black Dragon by banishing Seyfert
    • Link Black Dragon into Striker Dragon
    • chain link 1: Striker Dragon; chain link 2: Black Dragon
      • add White Dragon to your hand
      • add Boot Sector Launch to your hand
    • special summon White Dragon by banishing Black Dragon
    • Link White Dragon and Striker Dragon into Romulus
    • activate Romulus effect ⇒ add Ravine to your hand
    • activate Ravine
    • activate Ravine's effect ⇒ send 1 card to the GY ⇒ send Absorouter to the GY
    • activate Absorouter's effect ⇒ add Rokket Tracer to your hand
    • activate Boot Sector Launch
    • activate Boot Sector Launch's effect ⇒ special summon Tracer
    • activate Tracer's effect ⇒ target Boot Sector Launch ⇒ special summon Recharger
    • Link Tracer and Striker to Elpy and Striker Dragon
      • Striker Dragon in the right of Romulus
      • Elpy in the middle position
    • activate Elpy's effect ⇒ special summon Dragonmaid
    • activate Dragonmaid's effect ⇒ add Tidying to your hand
    • activate Striker Dragon's effect ⇒ target Elpy
    • add Recharger to your hand
    • activate Recharger's effect ⇒ target Elpy ⇒ special summon Tracer
    • Link Dragonmaid into Pisty
    • activate Pisty's effect ⇒ target the banished Seyfert ⇒ special summon it
    • Synchro summon Borreload Savage from Tracer and Seyfert
    • activate Savage's effect ⇒ target Striker Dragon
    • final: Borreload Savage (1 neg) + Romulus (extra monster zone) + Pisty (in the left of Romulus) + Striker Dragon (in the right of Romulus)
      • Striker Dragon and Pisty, both of then point to the same spot = pressure
Final consideration: if you don't have resources to make any kind of combo, just try to make Hieratic Seal and Pass

deck_excerpt: This deck aims to get 10 counters on Gizmek Legend - Kamitsukawashiime-no-Kikie, so that you negate the effects of your opponents monsters.
deck_description: This deck is an idea for the new Gizmek support we are getting. The Field Spell negates the effects of monsters on either side of the field if they don't have the same ATK & DEF, as long as you have Special Summoned 10 Machine monsters with the same ATK & DEF. I found that Deskbots are extremely good at swarming the field so you can easily get 10 Special Summons, and (thankfully) all have the same 500/500 ATK & DEF. This is a way I found to get to the win condition but is in no way the best way, so if you have any other way to get the 10 counters, please share the combo line so that this deck can be fine-tuned.  The best combo line I found is Deskbot 003 summon 001 go into Halq, Halq summon 001, go into Auroradon, summon 3 tokens then summon both copies of 001 from GY and turn 1 001 and all tokens into Deskbot Jet. Jet pop a Deskbot monster to Special Summon 1 from Deck and from there try to get the last 1-2 counters you dont have by whatever you have in yout hand or field. This all has to be done while having the Gizmek Field Spell face-up ON YOUR FIELD.

deck_excerpt: Pieces of Exodia hidden Behind Red-Eyes Dark Dragoon
deck_description: Deck Focus is to ultimately draw all pieces of Exodia and win the duel. The strategy is to use negate effects to deter your opponent from playing their game... sort of like control. The main card of this deck is , you would want to get him on the field as soon as you can. His effect must be used wisely since it is once per turn. The spells in this deck allow you to draw and that is a side purpose. Mystic mine and field barrier protect you from attacks since the current meta that focuses on swarming. The Nobleman helps banish traps and spells and banishes all traps named like it. Judgment of Anubis helps protect your spells and traps, and so does Ultimate Providence; The card is beastly since its a speed 3 and a counter. The side deck is self explanatory, hand traps and backboard destroyer. The Solemns' are for further negation and destruction. Card destruction and Pot of Benevolence are there to aid and are semi necessary if you'd like. The extra deck has Number 39: Utopia to negate attacks. Bujinki and the rest of the knightmares are fillers but one of each are still good if you plan to use their effects. Link Kuriboh helps and Dark Dragoon. I am constantly changing this deck to play better. My main goal is to attack the current meta and people's playstyle. Honestly, I am fed up with decks that rely on combos. Its become a little annoying to see people memorizing combos instead of building their own deck and succeeding that way. Call this deck what you want, but It has some thought put into it. Sadly, this deck will not appear in the Meta-Boards.

deck_excerpt: Using Mystic Mine to lock them in and Cauldron to burn them down, this deck works well to stop your opponent's strategy before it even touches the fie
deck_description: The strategy for this deck is to use cards such as Planet Pathfinder and Terraforming to search for Mystic Mine, as well as using other searchers such as Pot of Duality/Extravagance/Prosperity and Left Arm Offering to gather either Mine's protection (Field Barrier and Prohibition), and the namesake burn card, Cauldron of the Old Man. Just Desserts serves well as additional burn to help speed up the process.  Additional aid to this deck in regard to protection include Droll & Lock Bird, Summon Limit and Lose 1 Turn to stop combos, and Dark Bribe to stop negation.
